# Mira agent conventions

## Tooling

- Package manager: **Bun** (`bun install`, `bun run <script>`, `bunx`). See `use-bun-instead-of-node-vite-npm-pnpm.mdc` when editing package manifests.
- Lint: `bun run lint` (oxlint). Format: `bun run format` (oxfmt).
- Typecheck: `bun run typecheck` from root or per app.
- Project map and commands: **`AGENTS.md`** at repo root.

## Code changes

- Minimize scope — smallest correct diff; do not change unrelated code.
- Match existing conventions in the file and feature you touch.
- Named exports; function declarations for components (`function Foo()`).
- Use `type` for type-only exports.
- Comments only for non-obvious business logic — not on every line.

## Git

- **Do not commit** unless the user explicitly asks.
- **Do not push** unless the user explicitly asks.
- Follow git safety: no force push to main, no `--no-verify`, no amending pushed commits.

## App-specific patterns

Load automatically via glob rules — do not guess:

- `apps/desktop` → `mira-desktop-feature-patterns.mdc`
- `apps/web` → `mira-frontend-feature-patterns.mdc`, `mira-frontend-api-integration.mdc`
- `apps/online-order` → `mira-frontend-feature-patterns.mdc`, `mira-frontend-api-integration.mdc`
- `apps/backend` → `backend-modular-structure.mdc`
- `apps/mobile` → `mira-mobile-feature-patterns.mdc`

Skills in `.cursor/skills/` for deep task workflows (E2E, TanStack DB, transitions).

## Golden paths (quick)

| Area | First step |
|------|------------|
| Desktop feature | `@apps/desktop/src/features/orders/` or `tables/` + `mira-desktop-feature-patterns.mdc` |
| Web feature | `@apps/web/src/features/catalog/products/` + `mira-frontend-feature-patterns.mdc` |
| Online order feature | `@apps/online-order/src/features/` + `mira-frontend-feature-patterns.mdc` |
| Backend module | `@apps/backend/src/modules/customers/` + `backend-modular-structure.mdc` |
| Mobile feature | `@apps/mobile/src/features/home/` + `mira-mobile-feature-patterns.mdc` |
| E2E | `bun run e2e` + `e2e-desktop` skill |
| Stale `.cursor/plans/` | Read banner — treat as historical; trust `AGENTS.md` and live code |
